title: Stocks to watch during busiest week of earnings season
text: What the traders are watching next week during earnings. With CNBC's Courtney Reagan and the Fast Money traders, Tim Seymour, Karen Finerman, Steve Grasso and Guy Adami.

title: Uber could be the 'Facebook of 2020,' says RBC analyst
text: Some big technology companies are set to report earnings next week. Mark Mahaney of RBC Capital joins CNBC's "Power Lunch" to discuss what investors should watch.

title: Trump: I wouldn't be against Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg running for president
text: President Donald Trump sat down with CNBC's Joe Kernen at the Davos World Economic Forum in Switzerland about his thoughts on Facebook founder and CEO Mark Zuckerberg.

title: Facebook Stock Near High With Quarterly Earnings Report Coming Up
text:
With Facebook stock trading near record highs, the social media giant reports fourth-quarter earnings on Wednesday, as Wall Street analyst hope to get a clearer picture on the year ahead.

title: Facebook’s dodgy defaults face more scrutiny in Europe
text: Italy’s Competition and Markets Authority has launched proceedings against Facebook for failing to fully inform users about the commercial uses it makes of their data.

title: Investing in AI: A Beginner's Guide
text: Artificial intelligence is on track to be a truly revolutionary technology. Here's what investors need to know.

title: Italy watchdog threatens Facebook with another fine over improper use of data
text: Italy’s competition watchdog said on Friday it has launched proceedings against Facebook for non-compliance with a request to correct improper commercial practices in the group’s treatment of user data.

title: Soros: Facebook is conspiring to reelect Trump
text: “Facebook will work together to reelect Trump, and Trump will work to protect Facebook so that this situation cannot be changed, and it makes me very concerned about the outcome for 2020.”

title: George Soros Says Facebook is Conspiring to Re-Elect Donald Trump
text: Billionaire George Soros discusses Facebook Inc.’s involvement in U.S. elections and his fear that the company is working with President Donald Trump to get him re-elected. Soros spoke Thursday at the World Economic Forum’s annual meeting in Davos, Switzerland.

title: Earnings Outlook: Facebook earnings preview: Ready for another strong quarter
text: Facebook Inc. surges into its fourth-quarter earnings report Wednesday with some long-term questions.

title: Italy watchdog launches non-compliance proceedings against Facebook
text: Italy's competition watchdog has launched proceedings against Facebook for non-compliance with a previous request it had made regarding improper commercial practices in the group's treatment of user data, the agency said on Friday.
